4. What are HTML Entities? With Example.\par
\b0 -HTML entities are special characters that are used to display reserved characters in HTML. They are used to display characters that would otherwise be interpreted as HTML code, such as the less-than symbol (<) or the ampersand symbol (&). For example, the HTML entity for the less-than symbol (<) is &lt;, and the HTML entity for the ampersand symbol (&) is &amp;.\par
