6. What is the \lquote class\rquote  attribute in HTML? With Example.\par
-\b0 The 'class' attribute in HTML is used to specify a class for an element. Classes are used to group elements together and apply CSS styles to them. Multiple elements can have the same class, and an element can have multiple classes. Here's an example:\par
<p class="intro">This is a paragraph with the class "intro".</p>\par
<p class="intro">This is another paragraph with the class "intro".</p>\par
<p class="outro">This is a paragraph with the class "outro".</p>\par
In this example, the first two paragraphs have the class "intro", while the third paragraph has the class "outro".\par
\b\par
